texts.value: Induces translational repression through 28S ribosomal RNA cleavage in response to ER stress. Pro-apoptotic. Appears to play no role in the unfolded-protein response, unlike closely related proteins
The kinase domain is activated by trans-autophosphorylation. Kinase activity is required for activation of the endoribonuclease domain (By similarity)
Belongs to the protein kinase superfamily. Ser/Thr protein kinase family

features.description: Loss of autophosphorylation, of induction of apoptosis and of 28S rRNA cleavage, attenuation of repression of protein synthesis.
